text:
I'm at 4; the Mrs. says "3.5*." But the Mrs. is also a little sore that there were no crab legs. 

Visited for lunch on 12\/14\/16. Props on the splendid holiday decor. The only way I can think of to proceed, totally subjectively BtW, is to rank best & worst --

BEST:
-Pancakes + vanilla sweet cream + mixed berry butter. YUM!
-Sausages (Italian; spicy chicken; traditional Italian);
-Flank steak;
-Whipped potatoes;
-Chicken dumplings;
-Pork cutlet (from Italian Station);
-Beet salad;
-Berry-topped cheesecake;
-Creme brûlée;
-Cobbler;
-Butterscotch bread pudding;
-Strawberry cheesecake ice cream;

CONS\/ Did not enjoy:
-Seafood pasta -- shrimp & over cooked;
-Fried round mozzarella ball;
-WHERE IS THE FRUIT??
-Salmon served in Italian Line was way overcooked;
-Sweet & spicy chicken was gummy\/ squishy (not crisp), and not very flavorful;
-Shrimp was terrible & overcooked in shrimp & cheese grits;
-Rhubarb cobbler-meh.

Before you go judging, this was a shared operation b\/ t me & the wife. We stand by every word. Even so, this is a pretty good Buffet. Check it out for your last meal- then go catch a book & some zzzs from Mccarran & the flight home. That's what we did. Not a bad ending to Vegas.

My last meal in Vegas was to be at the Wynn Buffet. I know everyone has their ideas of who has the best buffet, and for the money Wynn was pretty good. 

